Povar <p><img src="http://members.home.net/eqnimphe/portal.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uylana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/22/01 4:26:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does Remove Curse spell exist yet?</span><hr size=1> (From Safehouse)<br>
There are 16 AE's that are considered as curses and will be cured by Remove Curse. Each of these spells have a curse counter (like poisons or disease AE's have poison/disease counter that make you cast your cure poison/disease spells several times)<br>
<br>
Spells with 1 curse counters<br>
Sun Revenant's Curse<br>
Curse of the Revenant<br>
Curse of Lord Wedazi<br>
<br>
Spells with 2 curse counters<br>
Balance of Zebuxoruk<br>
<br>
Spells with 3 curse counters<br>
Curse of Eternal Suffering<br>
Curse of Xerkizh<br>
Spirit Curse<br>
Deathly Chants<br>
Soul Curse<br>
Curse of Rhag`Zadune<br>
Touch of Zebuxorux<br>
<br>
Spells with 4 curse counters<br>
Feeblemind<br>
Itraer Vius Touch<br>
Serpentine Curse<br>
Shrieker's Curse<br>
<br>
Spells with 5 curse counters<br>
Touch of the Mistress <p><br>
<b>Ylana Mephistaii</b>
